As the district readjusts our plans additional information will be forthcoming regarding the start of school schedules and the calendar for the remainder of the year.

post_text: Grand Haven Area Public Schools stands against systemic racism. We will continue to support African Americans and all people of color, including those among our students and staff, to create an equitable and inclusive community. We call on all educational organizations, government, businesses, and our civil society to work for social justice across the United States of America and the world over. We all have work to do.

post_text:
On the evening of March 12, Governor Whitmer ordered the closure of all K-12 school buildings for three weeks, beginning Monday. Therefore, GHAPS will be closed March 16 – April 3, 2020. All buildings will be closed to students, which means there will be no activities or events at our schools. Daycare and Open Door are closed as well. Spring Break will proceed as scheduled from April 6 – 10, 2020.
We don’t have all the answers at this time, but we’re working nonstop to address the many complexities of this unprecedented situation. For more details, please visit https://www.ghaps.org/our-district/coronavirus-updates/.

post_text: At Lakeshore Middle School, Winterfest is a tradition to celebrate students, build relationships and to have fun in the long days of winter. shared_text:
Community Care for Teens

Steven VanderWerp Real Estate
December 16, 2019 at 11:30 AM ·

People are often surprised to learn that there are many homeless teens in the Grand Haven area. We started Community Care for Teens four years ago to raise awareness of their plight and to fill the need these kids experience, especially during Christmas. To give them hope, inspire and empower them, and let them know they’re not forgotten. This Holiday Season, give a homeless teen the gift of a Merry Christmas. To learn how you can help, please send me a message!
🏡#soldbystevo
🌐https://soldbystevo.com/
🏢@Home Realty, 1307 S Beacon Blvd, Grand Haven, MI 49417

post_text: Attention Parents! Rosy Mound Elementary is closed today. This morning, we received an anonymous tip through OK2SAY that there was a possible threat to the safety of our students at Rosy Mound. The information is vague, but we have decided to close Rosy Mound for the day. Students on buses are being taken to Lakeshore Middle School, and we're asking parents to pick their children up as soon as possible. More information will be provided to Rosy Mound parents via email. Thank you for helping us keep our students safe.

post_text: GHHS F.I.R.S.T. Robotics team finished their 2019 competition robot despite the harsh winter weather! Students and mentors rose to the challenge and are ready to compete in March.
